body.paragraph: A comparison that checks if the left item is not inside the right item. Some possible options: (1) The left item could be a number and the right item be a list of numbers. (2) The right item could be a text and the right item be a larger text or a list of texts.

body.example:
from random import randint
a = randint(1, 10)
b = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
if a in b:
	print("a is inside b")

if a not in b:
	print("a is not inside b")

tooltip.title: Inside?
tooltip.body: Returns True if the left item is inside the right item; returns False otherwise.
